
[1]white-pyrites

   WHITE-PYRITE, WHITE-PYRITES, n. [white and pyrite.] An ore of a
   tin-white color, passing into a brass-yellow and steel-gray, occurring
   in octahedral crystals, sometimes stalactitical and botryoidal. It
   contains 46 parts of iron, and 54 of sulphur.
